A tragic incident unfolded in Glendale as a man parked his SUV on the train tracks, causing a catastrophic collision involving multiple trains.
The death toll rose as rescuers navigated through the wreckage, with passengers recounting harrowing tales of survival.
The suspect, Juan Manuel Alvarez, faced murder charges for his actions, which resulted in at least 10 fatalities and numerous injuries.
Alvarez, who had a history of drug arrests and violence, initially intended to end his life but fled the scene when the train approached.
The community rallied together to aid the injured amidst the chaos.
